item.title: About
item.dc:creator: davidianshaw
item.content:encoded:
Questioning the status quo since 1969. Funny, but it's true. And it's my email signature. Ive always known I was a bit different and saw things in a different light than most people. born outside of Philadelphia, I spent my first 14 years in suburbia. Although, I never felt like I fit in. From a young a ge I was always conscious about the world around me, the delicate balance that life existed in. I hated seeing trash all over the place. I wanted people to think about what happens to that wrapper that just got thrown on the ground. I didn't know it then, but I was well on the path to becoming some type of leader championing change for good- that our environment was our house and we were messing things up. A move from the east coast west to Portland Oregon changed everything. Talk about culture shock. At first it was really hard. But over time I realized that the west coast culture "fit" me.

My interest lies in human problems where I like to provoke and inspire individuals/teams to think differently. Sometimes solutions to problems need different approaches to make sense of complexity. Im both a left-brain AND right-brain thinker and have experience coaching at all leadership levels, as well as mentoring junior team members. Over my career, I have worked across multiple business functions including R&D, Product, IT, and HR. Ive been an artist since childhood and have a strong belief in serious play.

Ask me about the weather. The answer might surprise you.
